  "title": "Processing Officer (Bank I East I Up to 4.5k)",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><ul><li>Opportunity to work for one of the leading financial service providers and top banks</li><li>Great exposure to learn about banking products and services domain</li><li>East Location</li></ul><p><strong>The Job</strong></p><ul><li>Process end‑to‑end chargeback cases for SG/HK across major card schemes</li><li>Perform eligibility checks, review documents and follow up with customers/merchants</li><li>Execute required chargeback actions (Retrievals, Chargebacks, Representments, Arbitration, Compliance)</li><li>Update case details and manage documents across internal systems and card platforms.</li><li>Handle financial adjustments (temp credits, reversals, deductions) and send relevant notifications</li><li>Create/reconcile GL entries and track outstanding cases through queues and reports</li><li>Manage case closures, rejection items, basic reconciliation, filing and report retrieval</li><li>Liaise with internal teams and Card Associations on enquiries, exceptions and rule clarifications</li><li>Support ad‑hoc projects, system testing, SOP updates and process improvements</li></ul><p><strong>The Talent</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 years’ exp in financial institutions; credit operations is an advantage</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft 365, especially Excel</li><li>Have a growth mindset</li><li>Able to multitask and manage multiple timelines</li><li>Strong team player with positive mindset and ability to work in a diverse environment</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Next Steps</strong></p><ul><li>Send your resume to <strong>yueshan.wu@adecco.com</strong></li><li>Email Topic: Processing Officer</li></ul><p><br />Wu Yue Shan<br />EA License No: 91C2918<br />Personnel Registration Number: R25138923</p>",
